# cloc configuration — read automatically from the current directory.
# Counts only hand-written source; skips dependencies, build artifacts,
# generated bindings, coverage reports, lockfiles, and release tooling.
#
# Invoke as either `cloc .` (auto-detects this file in cwd) or
# `cloc --config .clocrc .` if cloc's auto-discovery is disabled.
# `task cloc` uses the equivalent flags inline; keep the two in sync
# when you edit either.

# ── Dependency / vendor directories ──────────────────────────────────
#   node_modules/                  npm packages (frontend + transitive Go
#                                  flatted/golang/ stray pkg lives here)
#   vendor/                        Go vendored deps when present
# ── Build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   dist/                          Wails + server binary output
#   frontend/dist/                 Vite production bundle (caught by 'dist')
#   build/                         Wails build scaffold (icons, bin/, NSIS)
#   recall/                        produced binary's working dir if run in repo
#   data/                          local runtime data
# ── Generated source ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   wailsjs/                       Wails-generated Go↔JS bindings
#                                  (regenerated by `wails dev`)
# ── Test/coverage output ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#   coverage/                      Go coverage HTML + JSON
#   frontend/coverage/             Vitest V8 coverage HTML + lcov
#                                  (caught by 'coverage')
# ── VCS / editor ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   .git/                          cloc skips by default; explicit for clarity
#   .idea/, .vscode/               IDE config (often noise in line counts)
#   .devcontainer/                 dev-container scaffold (mostly JSON)
--exclude-dir=node_modules,vendor,dist,build,recall,data,wailsjs,coverage,.git,.idea,.vscode,.devcontainer

# Single generated files cloc would otherwise count:
#   go.sum                         Go module checksum DB
#   package-lock.json              npm dep lockfile
#   package.json                   skipped — counted upstream, not source
#   api.gen.d.ts                   openapi-typescript output (task gen-types)
#   App.js / models.ts (wailsjs)   already covered by --exclude-dir
#   CHANGELOG.md                   release-please autogen
#   .release-please-manifest.json  release-please state
--not-match-f=(go\.sum|package-lock\.json|api\.gen\.d\.ts|CHANGELOG\.md|\.release-please-manifest\.json)

# Skip a few binary/asset extensions cloc may otherwise try to read
# (cloc's default heuristics catch most; this is belt-and-suspenders).
--exclude-ext=png,jpg,jpeg,gif,ico,icns,woff,woff2,ttf,otf,pdf,db,sqlite

# Don't follow symlinks (the Podman VM and dev-container occasionally
# create loops via mounted volumes).
--no-symlinks

# Output format is deliberately NOT pinned here so `cloc .` produces
# the compact per-language summary. Use `task cloc-detail` (or pass
# `--by-file-by-lang` yourself) when you want the per-file breakdown.
